  "poem": {
    "content": "The olympic flame, a flash of gold,\nNever dims in April’s hold.\nA lazy sun upon the bay,\nAnother dawn begins to play.\n\nOne canvas bleached by salty air,\nWhere seabirds seek a life to share.\nI carry burdens, understood,\nExplain myself as best I could.\n\nMy body aches, a solemn plea,\nTo repair what’s broken in me.\nSo easily, the tides recede,\nA whispered promise, planted seed.\n\nNo succulent meat, just bone on bone,\nA lonely path, I walk alone.\nYet in the flash of breaking wave,\nThe strength I need, the courage crave.\n\nThat olympic spirit, fierce and bright,\nWill guide my soul through darkest night.\nAnd never let my spirit break.\nFor beauty's sake.",
